description: This column is about providing a description or summary of the company in the database. It may include details such as the company's mission, products or services, history, and any other relevant information.

This column stores the unique identifier for the provider associated with an authentication identity in the system. It likely links to the provider table or another source that contains details about the authentication providers used within the system.

This column is about storing the provider of the authentication identity associated with a user profile. It likely indicates the source or method used for user authentication, such as a social media platform (e.g., Google, Facebook) or an internal system.

This column contains the names of organizations or companies associated with the users in the system. It is likely used to store the names of different organizations or companies that users are affiliated with.
This column is about storing the first names of users in public profiles.
This column is a part of the 'profiles' table and stores the last names of users who have public profiles in the system. It is used to identify and distinguish users based on their last names.
This column is about storing the avatar or profile picture of each user in the system.
This column contains the email addresses of the user profiles within the system. It is used to store the contact information of the users for communication and identification purposes.
This column is about storing the phone number associated with a user's profile. It is likely used for contact purposes and communication within the system.
This column stores the names of the projects within the system. Projects may include various activities, tasks, or initiatives that users are working on or managing.

description: This column is about storing the user agent information associated with authentication sessions within the system. It likely includes details about the web browser or device used by the user when accessing the system.
This column is about tagging user sessions for authentication purposes within the system.
This column is used to store the identifier of the user entity, typically used for authentication purposes to uniquely identify a user within the system.

This column is about defining the role or privilege level of a user within the system. It likely specifies whether a user is an admin, a regular user, or has specific permissions related to managing profiles, companies, organizations, or projects.
This column is about storing the email address associated with a user's account for authentication and communication purposes.
This column is about storing the encrypted password of the user for authentication and security purposes. It is likely used to securely verify the user's identity during the login process.

This column stores the confirmation token for verifying user accounts when they sign up or make changes to their account details. It is used as a way to ensure the authenticity of the user's email address or other account information.
This column is used to store recovery tokens for users who may need to reset their password or recover their account access.
This column is used to store the new email change token for a user when they request to change their email address.
This column is about storing a token used to verify and confirm an email address change for a user in the system.
